<article class="env-example" id="003W">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/003W">Example <span data-tag="003W">6.2.1</span>.</a> Let $M=S^1$. Then $\widetilde{\operatorname{Bun}}_ G(M)\simeq G$, so $|\operatorname{Bun}_ G(M)|=\frac{1}{|G|} |\widetilde{\operatorname{Bun}}_ G(M)|=1$. For an element $g\in G$, the automorphism group of the corresponding bundle is the centralizer of $g$: $\operatorname{Aut}(P_ g)=Z_ g$; thus, </p>
  <div class="equation">
  \[  \frac{1}{|\operatorname{Aut}(P_ g)|}= \frac{|C_ g|}{|G|}  \]
</div>
  <p> where $C_ g\subset G$ is the conjugacy class containing $g$. </p>
</article>